OL,3,CWaiting list for routine NHS
OL,4,Ctreatments at lowest since 2022
OL,6,FSome 1.3% of people on the list for
OL,7,Fhospital treatment had been waiting
OL,8,Fmore than 52 weeks in March, down from
OL,9,F1.7% the previous month.
OL,11,FWhen it came to delays in A&E, the
OL,12,Fnumber of people waiting more than 12
OL,13,Fhours to be admitted stood at 47,750
OL,14,Fin April, up slightly from 46,665 in
OL,15,FMarch.
OL,17,FThe figure is still much lower than
OL,18,Fthe record 71,517 people recorded in
OL,19,FJanuary.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
